    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.\r\n\r\nPython is using squared brackets for specifying complex types - e.g. `tuple[int]`, `Callable[[int]`, `Union[int, str]`. It would be nice that Cython can follow this for `cython.pointer`:\r\n\r\n```python\r\na: cython.pointer[cython.Py_ssize_t]\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n### Describe the solution you'd like.\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Describe alternatives you've considered.\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Additional context\r\n\r\nOld behaviour `cython.pointer(...)` will be deprecated but still maintained for backward compatibility.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "This feels reasonable to me given the Python syntax.\r\n\r\nThe only question would be if it's easy to support both syntaxes (without having tried, I could imagine it might be fiddly).",
